    <etym xml:lang="ru">Метатеза из %i*sfad-%i ← %i*spād-%i. Восходит к <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>*spāy- :
            *spāta-</w><gloss><q>насыщаться</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>становиться упитанным</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в каузативе</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="en">in causative
            form</note><gloss><q>насыщать</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Прош. причастие %ispāta-%i было
        взято в осетинском за основу наст. времени; стало быть, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>*spāy-</w></mentioned> относится формально к ос. %iᵆfsadyn%i, как,
        скажем, в <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>traho</w></mentioned> к <mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>tracto</w></mentioned>; ср. в этом отношении <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ūdyn"/>. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>spai- :
                    spata-</w><gloss><q>насыщаться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>sphāy-: sphāta-</w><gloss><q>жиреть</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>полнеть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в каузативе</note><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="en">in causative
        form</note><gloss><q>откармливать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>насыщать</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                ><lang/><w>спѣти</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
            ><lang/><w>спеть</w></mentioned>. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsædyn"/>
        ‘насыщаться’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsīs"/> ‘насыщение’.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр. 325</biblScope><biblScope
                xml:lang="en">p. 325</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref
                target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XII 266</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Metathesis from %i*sfad-%i ← %i*spād-%i. It traces back to <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>*spāy- : *spāta-</w><gloss><q>become
            full</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/><gloss><q>become
                    well-fed</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в каузативе</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in
                causative form</note><gloss><q>satiate</q></gloss></mentioned>, . A past participle
        %ispāta-%i was taken in Ossetic for the present tense stem; thus, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>*spāy-</w></mentioned> is formally related to Ossetic %iᵆfsadyn%i, as,
        for example, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>traho</w></mentioned> is related to
            <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>tracto</w></mentioned>; cf. in this relation <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_ūdyn"/>. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>spai- :
                spata-</w><gloss><q>become full</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>sphāy-: sphāta-</w><gloss><q>fatten</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>put on weight</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в каузативе</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="en">in causative
            form</note><gloss><q>feed</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>satiate</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                ><lang/><w>спѣти</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                    ><lang/><w>спеть</w><gloss><q>ripen</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_7fsædyn"/> ‘become full’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsīs"/>
                ‘satiation’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр.
                325</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">p. 325</biblScope></bibl>. —
                <bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XII
                266</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
